% BEAVRS Cycle 1 full-core PWR - Serpent 2 translation (community example deck)
% =====================================================================
% PROVENANCE: Geometry + materials translated from the author-VERIFIED
% Cambridge SCONE BEAVRS full-core deck and the public MIT BEAVRS rev
% 2.0.2 specification (CRPG/MIT, 2018). COMMUNITY EXAMPLE DECK - NOT
% benchmark-validated; not an official MIT/CRPG product.
%
% CONTAINS: 17x17 core lattice (assembly pitch 21.50364 cm), 193 fuel
% assemblies on the verified BEAVRS loading map; 17x17 assemblies (pin
% pitch 1.26 cm, fuel 0.39218 / gap 0.40005 / clad 0.45720); enrichment
% zones 1.6/2.4/3.1 wt% UO2; per-assembly Pyrex burnable-poison clusters
% (real 6/12/15/16/20-rod patterns from the verified SCONE core); control
% rods WITHDRAWN (water-filled guide tubes); SS304 baffle/former plates,
% core barrel, 4 octant neutron-shield pads, downcomer, RPV.
%
% FULL AXIAL MODEL (this is the completed axial build; the older
% single-zone caveat is gone). Each pin type is an axial STACK of cells
% along z, ported layer-for-layer from the verified SCONE deck (z 0->460):
%  * active fuel z 36.748 -> 402.508 cm (height 365.76), continuous UO2,
%    segmented by 7 Inconel grid spacers + 1 plenum-region spacer;
%  * bottom water (0->20), lower core/support plate (20->35), Zircaloy
%    bottom end plug (35->36.748);
%  * top: upper fuel-rod plenum w/ Inconel spring (402.508->417.164, with
%    a spacer band), Zr top end plug (417.164->419.704), water
%    (419.704->423.049), SS304 top nozzle (423.049->431.876), water
%    (431.876->460);
%  * guide tubes: dashpot (narrowed thimble, sqc smaller radii) below
%    z~98, normal thimble above, borated-water support plate, 8 spacer
%    bands; instrument tube: bare thimble below support plate, full
%    thimble above; Pyrex BA rods: SS/dashpot transition + plenum
%    geometry above the poison column (Pyrex active z 40.558 -> 401.238).
%  Inconel grid spacers modeled as the verified deck's square Inconel
%  sleeve in the coolant (sqc half-widths 0.61015 -> 0.62992 cm) at the
%  8 BEAVRS spacer elevations.
%
% ASSUMPTIONS / SIMPLIFICATIONS (FLAGGED):
%  * ZAID suffix .06c assumed to mean 600 K (matching the verified SCONE
%    deck's JEF-3.1.1 .06 cards). Set 'set acelib' to a library whose
%    600 K suffix matches; energies are in MeV. Number densities are
%    identical to the verified deck.
%  * AXIAL and RADIAL models are both complete: per-assembly Pyrex BA
%    clusters, the stepped SS304 baffle/former, core barrel, four octant
%    neutron-shield pads, downcomer and RPV all ported from the verified
%    SCONE core. No radial simplifications remain.
%  * S(a,b) (therm lwtr) applied to WATER and borated-water support plate
%    only, never to UO2/structure.
%  * Run: sss2 -omp N beavrs_fullcore.sss
% =====================================================================

set title "BEAVRS Cycle 1 full-core PWR (Serpent translation, example deck)"

